item.dc:creator: @reyx7 reyx7
item.description:
@reyx7 wrote:

[quote=“R4z0rb14d3, post:14, topic:369264”][quote author=the wanderer link=topic=465396.msg3407303#msg3407303 date=1290407852]
Traced means you created a 3d spline and added faces to it. In other words you used the create line tool.
[/quote]

Ok yes then. Hmm, but how else can you make new models other than prim’ing? It was my understanding that “tracing” was the only way… which may be why i’m so confused about modeling armours. How the heck could people correctly shape armour via “tracing”…?[/quote]

Tutorial in my siggy
Trust me, you’ll find primitive modeling more efficient once you care about your polygon flow.

Yeah, I know. Just nobody has wanted my models so I kinda wanted to make one that people might want. Just wanted to make sure there were no overlaps or weird looking “fuzzy” faces near the hand.
